-- 
Woman Dies in Fire on U.K. Train Line, Sky Reports

-- B y   B l a n c h e   G a t t
-- 
2011-04-11T20:27:34Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-11/woman-dies-in-fire-on-u-k-west-coast-train-line-sky-reports.html
(Corrects operator of train in first paragraph.)  A woman died in a fire that broke
out on a train operated by London Midland on the U.K.’s West
Coast mainline at 4:25 p.m., local time, today on a run from
Northampton to London’s Euston station, as it approached
Leighton Buzzard station, in Bedfordshire, England, Sky News
reported, citing Network Rail Ltd.  Network Rail said in a statement on its website that it
received a report of a fire on board the train at 5 p.m. and
that one passenger was reported to be injured. The fire
department and police were at the scene, Network Rail said in
the statement. A call to Network Rail’s message service outside
office hours wasn’t immediately returned.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Blanche Gatt in London at 
 bgatt@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Colin Keatinge at 
 ckeatinge@bloomberg.net . 